    <h1>Welcome to Bioresource Process Control Engineering Research Group</h1>
    
    <p>
        The Bioresource Process Control Engineering Research Group was established in late 2022, following the completion of my PhD at the Department of Biosystems Machinery Engineering, Chungnam National University, Republic of Korea.
    </p>
    
    <p>
        Our research group is currently based in the Department of Agricultural and Biosystems Engineering, Universitas Gadjah Mada, Yogyakarta, Indonesia (<a href="https://tpb.tp.ugm.ac.id/en/homepage-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Go To</a>). Our research focuses on the application of process engineering, sensing technologies, mathematical modelling, automation, and intelligent control systems in the agricultural, food, and bioresource sectors.
    </p>
    
    <p>
        We are particularly interested in developing non-destructive sensing and data-driven approaches for monitoring, evaluating, and controlling biological and agricultural processes. Our research activities include near-infrared spectroscopy, hyperspectral imaging, machine learning, process optimisation, postharvest engineering, and the development of smart systems for agricultural and food applications.
    </p>
    
    <p>
        Through interdisciplinary research and collaboration, we aim to contribute to the development of efficient, sustainable, and intelligent technologies for the management and utilisation of biological resources.
    </p>

